The joy of parents watching their daughter grow into a lady and be successful is the happiest moment in life, just like walking her into marriage, a major event in life which is the only happiness the parents can ask for their daughter. Come next month, the renowned aviation guru, Captain Chris Onakorame Najomo and his darling wife, Martha Eseoghene will be hosting the wedding ceremony of their daughter, Carmille Omoigho Najomo and her heartthrob, Christian Chukwudizie, the son of Sir Chris Ikeliani and Lady Ngozi Ikeliani, on Saturday, June 4, at the Oriental Hotel, Lekki-Epe Expressway, Victoria Island, Lagos. The solemnisation of the holy matrimony holds on Saturday, June 11, at the Cathedral Church of Advent, Life Camp, Abuja. The reception will follow at Abuja International Conference Centre, Garki District. The bride, Carmille is a lawyer, based in the United States of America, while her husband-to-be, Christian Ikeliani, is an engineer, and works with Meta (Facebook) in the US. The couple met through mutual friends some years ago. The very classy wedding will attract the creme-de-la-crème of Nigerian society. The father of the bride, Captain Najomo, is a director at the Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority (NCAA) and her mother, Martha Najomo is the CEO of Seraphina Gems, an upscale outfit that stocks some of the most exotic jewellery in the world.